WEBVTT

00:02.258 --> 00:15.037
So they say here, noising student, when the student is deliberately noised, it is trained to be consistent to the teacher that is not noised when it generates the pseudo labels.

00:15.899 --> 00:22.849
In our experiments, we use two types of noise, input noise and model noise.

00:25.546 --> 00:36.461
First, data augmentation is an important noisy method in noisy student training because it forces the student to ensure prediction consistency across augmented versions of an image.

00:37.082 --> 00:48.297
Specifically in our method, the teacher produces high quality pseudo labels by reading in clean images while the student is required to reproduce those labels with augmented images as an input.

00:50.099 --> 01:04.003
Second, when dropout and stochastic depth function are used as noise, the teacher behaves like an ensemble at inference time when it generates pseudo labels, whereas the student behaves like a single model.

01:05.125 --> 01:09.232
In other words, the student is forced to mimic a more powerful ensemble model.

01:09.252 --> 01:11.095
We present an ablation study.

01:11.075 --> 01:13.641
So it's a bit weird what they say here.

01:14.422 --> 01:15.244
Don't be confused.

01:15.405 --> 01:20.356
You use the dropout and the stochastic depth on the student model.

01:21.258 --> 01:28.273
And they say here, if you do this, the teacher behaves like an ensemble at inference time.

01:28.253 --> 01:30.879
whereas the student behaves like a single model.

01:31.621 --> 01:36.050
It's a bit of a weird formulation, but it's true.

01:36.111 --> 01:47.055
The teacher will produce the same label for different pathways through the student if you use dropout and stochastic depth.

01:47.035 --> 01:57.074
And therefore the student is kind of required to approximate each time, each forward pass has a different forward pass through the layers, through the connections with dropout.

01:57.495 --> 02:03.106
And it's forced to approximate that teacher label with all of these different things.

02:03.587 --> 02:08.276
So you see that you put in a lot of techniques.

02:08.616 --> 02:10.039
So they have even other techniques.

